HEADWORD: Cursorial
<hw>Cur*so"ri*al</hw> <pr>(k?r-s?"r?-<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Adapted to running or walking, and
not to prehension; <as>as, the limbs of the horse are
<ex>cursorial</ex></as>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Aves</er>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to the <ord>Cursores</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cursorily</ent>⟦br⟧
